Adult.description: Yellow-billed Cuckoos have entirely white underparts while Mangrove Cuckoos have peachy underparts. The bill on Yellow-billed Cuckoos is entirely yellow, but is bicolored on Mangrove Cuckoos.
Black-billed Cuckoos have entirely white underparts while Mangrove Cuckoos have peachy underparts. The bill on black-billed Cuckoos is entirely black, but is bicolored on Mangrove Cuckoos.
